[SN]TITLE[SN]
Dockers Club: Fourteen held after Liverpool petrol bomb disturbance

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Nine men and five women have been arrested by police investigating a disturbance in which a petrol bomb was thrown at officers outside a club.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Merseyside Police raided 10 homes in the Anfield area of Liverpool.
Four officers were treated for minor burns after Tuesday's incident outside the Dockers Club in Townsend Lane.
Supt Mark Morgan said officers had "a lot of support" from the community, and promised that increased patrols would continue in the area.
