All 14 were arrested on drugs charges, police said.
One of the men was also held on suspicion of possession of a firearm in relation to a previous offence and another was held on suspicion of burglary.
One of the women was arrested on suspicion of breach of the peace and obstructing police.
On Thursday, a man was charged with resisting arrest and a drugs offence in relation to the incident.
He appeared before magistrates and was remanded in custody until next month, when he will appear at Liverpool Crown Court.
